        <ab>FOR GOD SO</ab>
        <ab>LOVED THE</ab>
        <ab>WORLD THAT</ab>
        <ab>HE GAVE HIS</ab>
        <ab>ONLY BEGOTTEN</ab>
        <ab>SON THAT</ab>
        <ab>WHOSOEVER</ab>
        <ab>BELIEVETH IN</ab>
        <ab>HIM SHOULD</ab>
        <ab>NOT PERISH</ab>
        <ab>BUT HAVE</ab>
        <ab>EVERLASTING</ab>
        <ab>LIFE</ab>
        <ab rend="Alignl">
          <note> the above written on a book</note>
        </ab>
        <ab/>
        <ab>THOMAS H. BRUCE</ab>
        <ab>BORN AT NEWCASTLE UPON TYNE AUGUST 9 1813.</ab>
        <ab>DIED AT ROME MAY 24 1881</ab>
        <ab>HAVING DEVOTED THE LAST 21 YEARS</ab>
        <ab>OF HIS LIFE TO THE WORK OF</ab>
        <ab>THE BRITISH &amp; FOREIGN BIBLE SOCIETY</ab>
        <ab>AS THEIR AGENT IN ITALY PS.89 12.</ab>
        <ab/>
        <ab>THIS TABLET WAS ERECTED</ab>
        <ab>IN LOVING REMEMBERANCE BY HIS CHILDREN</ab>
      </div>
      <div type="inscription" xml:lang="en" decls="#f_S #c_3 #m_I #t_P">
        <ab>ALSO IN LOVING MEMORY OF HIS WIFE</ab>
        <ab>ROSAMOND BRUCE</ab>
        <ab>BORN AT PAISLEY OCTOBER 12 1823</ab>
        <ab>DIED AT FLORENCE NOVEMBER 22 1897.</ab>
      </div>
